Going through the Crack ruins the experience due to litter, impoliteness, and well it's nearing the end of you're going clockwise.

name: Killarney Provincial Park
review:

name: Killarney Provincial Park
review:
As a park is amazing.
But the rangers need more training.
Not enough information of which camps are free. They said... go and see and if is occupied then paddle to next one (Lake George camps).
They need a better system.
But, once in nature that human factor is not relevant anymore.

review: Amazing & beautiful park. It is worth to drive around 4 + hours from Toronto. We camp near George lake and beach is so nice. There are small cliffs even kids can dive to water. If you are hiking don't miss granite trail (start near the park office ) , you can spot even Manitoulin island and light house too.

name: Killarney Provincial Park
review: So beautiful. The backcountry trails are challenging and the campsites lovely. Recommend fall when mosquitos and black flies are absent.

name: Killarney Provincial Park
review: Killarney has a well-deserved reputation as a spectacular wilderness park. It doesn't matter which direction you enter the park from.  It's all beautiful. The white quartzite of the La Cloche mountains never fails to impress. Unspoiled beauty and no crowds are a great combination. Enjoy!
